aws:cdk:cloudformation:props.description: This rule triggers the WHLambda function every 30 minutes.

aws:cdk:cloudformation:props.alarmDescription: Alarm when the availability metric is below 1 for https://www.youtube.com
Alarm when the latency metric is above 250ms for https://www.youtube.com
Alarm when the Response size metric is above 20000 bytes for https://www.youtube.com
Alarm when the availability metric is below 1 for https://www.google.com
Alarm when the latency metric is above 250ms for https://www.google.com
Alarm when the Response size metric is above 20000 bytes for https://www.google.com
Alarm when the availability metric is below 1 for https://www.instagram.com
Alarm when the latency metric is above 250ms for https://www.instagram.com
Alarm when the Response size metric is above 20000 bytes for https://www.instagram.com
